name: Eugenia pyxidata (J.Guého & A.J.Scott) N.Snow
eventRemarks: Tree 4m x 10cm. Buds globose, to 1cm diam. Leaves discolorous. Locally common. Rainfall 2600mm.
habitat: Degraded wet forest with Sideroxylon, invaded by exotics.

name: Eugenia pyxidata (J.Guého & A.J.Scott) N.Snow
eventRemarks: Canopy tree 5m x 10cm. Fruits submature, globose, green, to 20mm dia., with up to four seeds. Common locally.
habitat: Low degraded cloud forest invaded by exotics. Rainfall 5000mm

name: Eugenia pyxidata (J.Guého & A.J.Scott) N.Snow
eventRemarks: Fallen tree 12m x 30cm, crown compact. Bark smooth, pale gray, flaking irregularly. Flowers white with creosote odor. Fruits green, buds pale brown. Occasional locally.
habitat: lower montane rain forest with Calophyllum abundant.

name: Eugenia pyxidata (J.Guého & A.J.Scott) N.Snow
eventRemarks: Tree 5m, buds calyptrate, 1cm diam. Flowers white with strong creosote odor. Fruits green, 1.2cm diam. Locally common along summit ridge.
habitat: Low cloud forest with Nuxia and Monimiaceae highly invaded by exotics. Rainfall 5000mm. Summit ridge.
